WEBVTT

00:01.280 --> 00:04.158
I am not a number. I am a free man.

00:04.240 --> 00:05.275
You what?

00:05.360 --> 00:08.157
Well, Rachel's on her way to New York.
I can come and play.

00:08.240 --> 00:12.995
I'll pick you up in 20 minutes.
- That's the spirit, young man!

00:17.080 --> 00:18.798
Oh, hi, Pete.

00:18.880 --> 00:20.518
Yeah. Oh.

00:20.600 --> 00:22.511
I thought I might play golf this morning.

00:22.600 --> 00:26.195
David, you always get pissed off
when me and Adam do things without you.

00:26.280 --> 00:28.236
We were only saying this last night.

00:28.320 --> 00:30.117
What were you doing last night?

00:30.200 --> 00:32.191
We'll pick you up in 20, all right, mate?

00:39.360 --> 00:42.989
Come on, hurry up, David's waiting.
- I know, I know, I just can't find my wallet.

00:43.080 --> 00:44.513
Why aren't you going?

00:44.640 --> 00:46.278
With Rachel?
- Yeah.

00:46.360 --> 00:49.272
And listen to her and Jenny
talk about babies for ten days?

00:49.360 --> 00:52.716
No, I'd rather stay here with you,
take Rachel's advice, have some fun.

00:52.800 --> 00:54.631
Oh, while you still can.

00:54.720 --> 00:56.870
Oh! Let's go.

01:03.320 --> 01:06.437
A car auction?
I thought we were going to have some fun.

01:06.520 --> 01:09.432
Have a look around. See what's tasty.

01:09.520 --> 01:13.115
It's Karen's birthday in a couple of days.
I still need to get her a present.

01:13.200 --> 01:16.749
What are you thinking, driving lessons?
- I could get her something special.

01:16.840 --> 01:18.831
No, she already has a car.

01:18.920 --> 01:20.956
Not a Ferrari, she hasn't.

01:22.640 --> 01:24.995
Now, that is not a bad idea.

01:25.760 --> 01:27.159
Wheee!

01:28.880 --> 01:30.108
Oh, Karen.

01:30.200 --> 01:32.156
This is just like olden times, eh?

01:32.240 --> 01:33.673
You know?

01:33.760 --> 01:35.591
Now David's home.

01:35.680 --> 01:38.069
Well, there's certainly more washing.
- Yeah.

01:38.160 --> 01:40.390
But I don't know. It's nice.

01:40.480 --> 01:42.357
Maybe it's because I'm Catholic.

01:42.440 --> 01:46.274
But from the bottom of my heart,
I do believe in the sanctity of marriage.

01:46.360 --> 01:49.716
You don't have to be Catholic to believe that.
Just single.

01:49.800 --> 01:52.314
No, I do believe it.

01:54.160 --> 01:55.229
Hello?

01:56.080 --> 01:57.911
Mark. Hello.

02:02.000 --> 02:04.434
Not a subject I'd normally um...

02:05.360 --> 02:07.920
But Karen and I,
we actually had sex the other night.

02:08.000 --> 02:09.274
Ah! Ha, ha!

02:09.360 --> 02:11.555
It started as a massage.

02:11.640 --> 02:12.914
Was it good?

02:13.000 --> 02:15.150
Yes, my back had been...
- The sex.

02:15.240 --> 02:16.878
Oh, I see. Well...

02:16.960 --> 02:19.394
Um, how much detail do you want?

02:21.160 --> 02:22.752
Oh, my God.
- What?

02:22.840 --> 02:25.434
Well, Rachel's away, Pete's inactive.

02:25.520 --> 02:27.750
You're the only one who was having sex.

02:28.880 --> 02:30.791
Yes. The same thing had occurred to me, too.

